{"disposition":"accepted","experiment_id":"WM-001","findings":[{"id":"F001","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The v1.18 terminal evidence establishes the proximate failure as the sealed 600-second independent-audit deadline: it records zero stdout, zero stderr, no return code, no reviewed gate, and zero adjudication replay. Version 1.19 correctly treats the missing production-scale liveness qualification as the deeper harness defect and makes no scientific inference from that engineering failure."},{"id":"F002","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Audit-runtime-manifest v2 closes execution_role to conformance or outcome_audit, binds them to exactly 600 or 10,800 seconds, removes caller-selected timeout authority, and requires successful captured-audit-execution v2 receipts to contain a strict-positive runner-measured subprocess_elapsed_ns."},{"id":"F003","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Development qualification executes the complete outcome audit twice and requires byte equality of report, stderr, runtime manifest, and invocation manifest. Audit-reproduction v3 binds both exact execution-receipt files, byte counts, digests, elapsed values, producer-manifest identity, and the nested capacity record; closure preserves both receipts as explicit archive members."},{"id":"F004","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The capacity gate uses the slower authenticated development execution and separately ceiling-divides a safety-two projection to the sealed 8 GiB producer limit and 2 GiB result limit before addition. The exact timeout boundary is accepted, one additional nanosecond is rejected, and one byte beyond either size ceiling is rejected."},{"id":"F005","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The launcher, central verifier, independent artifact auditor, and adjudicator reopen canonical archive bytes, producer manifest, runtime and producer-target invocation manifests, and both durable elapsed receipts, join their identities, and independently recompute the capacity arithmetic. Adjudication performs this check while loading upstream evidence and before any formal replay launch."},{"id":"F006","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Formal audit and the sole permitted ordinary-report adjudication replay use outcome_audit custody. Adjudication-audit-execution v3 retains the replay elapsed value, ordinary reports receive exactly one byte-equality replay, and authenticated no-report failures receive zero replay and can only yield rejected evidence."},{"id":"F007","resolution":"resolved","severity":"minor","summary":"Composition regressions cover role and timeout mismatch, receipt shape and digest joins, stdout and stderr equality, exact archive membership including both execution receipts, canonical invocation target, call order, arithmetic boundaries, and stale-schema rejection. The plan and runbook now describe the exact eleven evidence roles and current schema versions."},{"id":"F008","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Scientific continuity is preserved: the sealed digest of all 17 scientific protocol blocks is unchanged, learning.py, model.py, planning.py, and runtime_lane.py retain their prior kernel bytes, formal scientific contracts remain unchanged, and v1.19 uses a fresh collision-checked seed domain."},{"id":"F009","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"Artifact sizes and full-auditor elapsed times are engineering calibration evidence only. The linear byte projection plus factor-two reserve is a prospective conservative liveness contract, not proof that a future audit must finish and not evidence for any scientific endpoint; any same-version failure remains terminal."},{"id":"F010","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The declared trust model remains local exact-byte and append-only custody rather than tamper resistance against a privileged adversary. Acceptance is scoped to that explicit model and does not broaden the scientific claim."},{"id":"F011","resolution":"resolved","severity":"minor","summary":"Independent final validation observed a valid sealed protocol, a clean exact 13-file runtime mypy gate, clean relevant Ruff and diff checks, 255 passing launcher-adjudication-operator integration tests, and 9 passing focused role, elapsed, capacity, and independent-consumer tests."},{"id":"F012","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"A future hardening change should expand the real central-verifier/adjudicator archive fixture beyond its valid case and wrong-invocation mutation to mutate elapsed digests, role and timeout, JSON type aliases, extra fields, and arithmetic at those exact consumer seams. Existing boundary and artifact mutation tests plus direct source-parity review make this a regression-depth recommendation, not an unresolved acceptance blocker."},{"id":"F013","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"This review examined source, schemas, authenticated failure metadata, engineering sizes and timing semantics, and test behavior without opening or reporting any prior or current scientific performance value."}],"implementation_files":[{"bytes":1685,"path":"Makefile","sha256":"8762bc79d3929716bdc0ae495cc3d2bb79fadb02812d092d00fff9330f022e1c"},{"bytes":148,"path":"bench/__init__.py","sha256":"6c7b9de75c247ced5f62064f9786cf6e2f14d958bd1be6eb65c6ed69680b6942"},{"bytes":561,"path":"bench/epistemic/__init__.py","sha256":"bb77dc8aba3b32b6bc2df16a5abd9fc24b0ece2a389e814c3337a0f637a5467e"},{"bytes":44718,"path":"bench/epistemic/lifecycle.py","sha256":"3d30d947ca830a0c307f2e7f40d31bc4bef51d497f2e96d68f000fa864e3ed25"},{"bytes":30661,"path":"bench/epistemic/maturity.py","sha256":"2a81abe60f12285f66f2bcd351589de28851412f1d9df7f2003843a845a2510e"},{"bytes":13611,"path":"bench/epistemic/problem.py","sha256":"c66ae13d3e833ffd1be1562a89e0e9035d6197b95723179b930c1ca2a1059c66"},{"bytes":1097,"path":"b